<DATELINE>JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> has a respected new ally in his presidential campaign: Sen. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, who hopes his <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> endorsement will end speculation about a last-minute <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> bid. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> picked up fellow Democrat <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON>'s endorsement here Wednesday. The two held a news conference near the Statue of Liberty staged to highlight the presidential hopeful's immigrant roots. <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> said he believes the <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> governor is the best Democrat to beat <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> front-runner <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>. `` I believe <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> can win. I believe he will be the next president of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> told a crowd of reporters and supporters at Liberty State Park. The senator promised to campaign for <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> both in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> _ which holds its primary on June 7 _ and around the nation. <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> said <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> can defeat the vice president `` because he is tenacious, innovative, resilient and disciplined.'' `` This is a very important endorsement because it comes from one of the most respected and one of the most accomplished public figures in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> today,'' <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> said, adding that <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> would be `` very, very important to our success.'' <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> said he hoped the endorsement would end talk about his entering the race. The senator, a former Rhodes scholar and <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORG