<BYLINE>By MARY SEDOR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HEBRON, Occupied West Bank (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli troops shot dead an Arab today and wounded four others, including a 12-year-old, in clashes across the occupied territories, hospital officials said. Overnight, troops swept through the occupied lands in a mass arrest of Palestinians. <PERSON> Majid </PERSON> <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Ahmed </PERSON> <PERSON> Sawalma </PERSON>, 21, died of two bullet wounds to the chest and heart during a clash in the <LOCATION> Balatta </LOCATION> refugee camp near <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Al </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ittihad </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> officials said. Among the four Palestinians wounded in scattered clashes frm <LOCATION> Hebron </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION> was a 12-year-old girl from the village of <LOCATION> Tamoun </LOCATION>, 10 miles west of <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>, the officials said. Arab media reports said troops were using several <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> schools as detention centers. The army said it was checking the reports of casualties and declined to comment on reports that schools were being used as detention centers. In <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> warplanes attacked <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> guerrilla bases on the outskirts of <LOCATION> Sidon </LOCATION> for the second straight day. There was no immediate word on casualties. It was the third Israeli strike against Palestinian bases in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> in a week and the fifth this year. Because of the ongoing violence in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, Monsignor <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> <PERSON> Sabbah </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> patriarch, decided to cancel the traditional Palm Sunday procession from the Mount of Olives to <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>'s