nd estimated the actual number of arrests in the past four days in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> at about 350. An Islamic official in <LOCATION> Hebron </LOCATION> said <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers had detained more than 150 imams, or Moslem religious leaders, in nighttime roundups this week. The official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said most of those detained were members of the fundamentalist Islamic Jihad movement. The army has confirmed it is making arrests but has refused to give details. Israeli officials have said the tactic has reduced Arab violence. The patriarch decided to suspend this Sunday's procession because of the possibility of violence along its narrow, winding route through <LOCATION> Arab </LOCATION> <LOCATION> east </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>, said the Rev. <PERSON> Cladio </PERSON> <PERSON> Baratto </PERSON>, director of the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Information </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> Old </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. The procession commemorates <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON>' entry into <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> before his crucifixion. `` Prudence suggests this decision. It was a personal decision of the Patriarch and no other forces influenced him,'' <PERSON> Baratto </PERSON> told The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Baratto </PERSON> denied reports that <PERSON> Sabbah </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>'s first Arab patriarch for Latin-rite Catholics, had been pressured by the underground leadership of the Palestinian unrest to call off the ceremony, which has been canceled only three times since 1932. <PERSON> Baratto </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> Jerusalem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> there were fears that Christians from the occupied territories would be prevented from attending due to curfews. On Tuesday, <ORGANIZATION> D