<HEAD>Four Cultural Revolution Military Leaders Out of Prison</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHY WILHELM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Four military leaders imprisoned for an alleged coup attempt against <PERSON> Mao </PERSON> <PERSON> Tse-tung </PERSON> in 1971 have been released, a government spokesman said today. All four were top assistants to Defense Minister <PERSON> Lin </PERSON> <PERSON> Piao </PERSON> during the ultra-leftist Cultural Revolution that began in 1966, and all were convicted of aiding him in an aborted attempt to murder <PERSON> Mao </PERSON> and seize power. The releases leave only the `` Gang of Four'' still in prison from among the 10 fallen Cultural Revolution power brokers convicted in 1981 after a lengthy show trial. <PERSON> Lin </PERSON> was <PERSON> Mao </PERSON>'s designated successor, a key creator of the <PERSON> Mao </PERSON> cult and author of the `` Little Red Book'' of quotations from <PERSON> Mao </PERSON>. He allegedly died in a plane crash in <LOCATION> Mongolia </LOCATION> while fleeing arrest. <PERSON> Zeng </PERSON> <PERSON> Tao </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s legislature, disclosed the releases at a news conference. He said former air force commander <PERSON> Wu </PERSON> <PERSON> Faxian </PERSON>, former navy political commissar <PERSON> Li </PERSON> <PERSON> Zuopeng </PERSON> and former army Gen. <PERSON> Jiang </PERSON> <PERSON> Tengjiao </PERSON> were released on bail for medical treatment, but he did not say when or disclose the nature of their illnesses. <PERSON> Qiu </PERSON> <PERSON> Huizuo </PERSON>, former director of the military's <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Logistics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>, completed his 16-year term in September and was released, <PERSON> Zeng </PERSON> said. He did not explain why as recently as January, the <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <O