<HEAD>Contest Jurors Stymied in Picking Best Novel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Jurors could n't decide on the best English-language novel this year, so the $ 50,000 prize in the <ORGANIZATION> Ritz </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hemingway </ORGANIZATION> literary contest will go to charity, it was announced Thursday. The three nominees for this year's annual prize were the South African writer <PERSON> Nadine </PERSON> <PERSON> Gordimer </PERSON> for `` A Sport of Nature,'' <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> novelist <PERSON> Toni </PERSON> <PERSON> Morrison </PERSON> for `` Beloved,'' and `` In the Skin of a Lion,'' by Canadian writer <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Ondaatje </PERSON>. `` To choose the best novel of the year is always a difficult task,'' said <PERSON> Pierre </PERSON> <PERSON> Salinger </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> journalist who served as jury president. `` This year, three excellent authors of great reputation were nominated. But none of the works received a majority of the votes from the 10 jurors.'' The contest's rules thus call for the money to go to charity. Half was donated to the <ORGANIZATION> Georges </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pompidou </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>, which helps the elderly. The other half went to the <ORGANIZATION> Franco-American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Volunteer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, which helps handicapped children get involved in sports. The first <ORGANIZATION> Ritz </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hemingway </ORGANIZATION> award was given in 1985 to Peruvian writer <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Vargas </PERSON> <PERSON> Llosa </PERSON>. The other winners were <PERSON> Marguerite </PERSON> <PERSON> Duras </PERSON> of <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON> of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>.
