<HEAD>Six Arrested at Cryonics Lab Sue County</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Six members of a laboratory group who were detained during a search for a missing frozen head have filed false arrest claims with the county totaling $ 225,000. The six claims, filed individually at various times this month, stem from the December beheading of 83-year-old <PERSON> Dora </PERSON> <PERSON> Kent </PERSON> so her head could be frozen to preserve it for theoretical revival using as-yet undiscovered medical techniques. The six members of the <ORGANIZATION> Alcor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Life </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Extension </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> were detained by police Jan. 7 during a search of the premises. They were questioned at the police department then released. All six say they were arrested for investigation of obstruction of justice. Filing a claim is a preliminary step toward suing. <LOCATION> Riverside </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> has the option of settling the claims, or rejecting them after they are reviewed by claims adjustors. In one claim, five <ORGANIZATION> Alcor </ORGANIZATION> members contend they `` suffered emotional stress arising from the purposeful, wrongful conduct of the coroner's investigators.'' They seek damages totaling $ 125,000. The sixth person filed a separate claim for $ 100,000. During two searches at the lab, authorities found Mrs. <PERSON> Kent </PERSON>'s hands and some equipment allegedly stolen from the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> Her head never was found. Last month, the coroner's office ruled the woman's death a homicide, finding she had been killed by a lethal dose of barbiturates. <ORGANIZATION> Alcor </ORGANIZATION> officials contend the woman was dead when they began their procedure. The case was sent to the district attorney's office, but Prosecutor <PERSON> Jay </PERSON> <PERSON> Thompson </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanks </PERSON> said Thursday no decision regarding charges has been made.
