new version exempts both companies with fewer than 50 workers and farms from having to continue paying wages and benefits for up to a year to workers ordered off the job because of the danger that might be raised by continued exposure to hazardous substances. It also puts restrictions on what information from the program could be used by workers and former workers in pursuing liability suits against employers. Democrats admitted that <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>'s parliamentary maneuver, although allowed by <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> rules, could be used to thwart Republicans from offering amendments of their own. But they maintained that was not the intent. `` I do n't think it's fair,'' said <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Democratic Leader <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON>, D-W. <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION> `` The parliamentary landscape has We've seen now how senators can be shut out from offering amendments circumstantially with no malice intended.
