<HEAD>Broken Bridge Leaves Hundreds Stranded In the Florida Keys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISLAMORADA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A broken drawbridge that stranded hundreds of motorists, some holding parties and others asleep in their cars, was fixed just in time for Thursday's morning rush-hour, police said. `` There are a lot of happy people out there,'' said <LOCATION> Monroe </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Sheriff's Sgt. <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Pinder </PERSON>. The <LOCATION> Snake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Creek </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bridge </LOCATION> reopened to traffic at 8:10 a.m. after several gears jammed on the bridge Wednesday and locked it in the upright position for more than 15 hours, snarling traffic for 30 miles on <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> 1, the main highway from <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Key </LOCATION> <LOCATION> West </LOCATION>. Every hotel room on both sides of the drawbridge at Plantation Key was taken, and hundreds of people spent the night in their cars. Police said motorists were remarkably patient. `` There were no arrests, no wrecks, no real problems,'' <PERSON> Pinder </PERSON> said. One man who suffered a mild heart attack had to be ferried across <LOCATION> Snake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Creek </LOCATION> to an ambulance, <PERSON> Pinder </PERSON> said. A crane arrived from Key West at about 1 a.m. Thursday, and two barges were brought in to aid state <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> workers who fixed the bridge, said <LOCATION> Monroe </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Sgt. <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Cockrell </PERSON>. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Rocheleau </PERSON>, 25, and his friend <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Kotval </PERSON>, 23, sat in their car at the front of the line going north. `` You just have to roll with the punches,'' said <PERSON> Rocheleau </PERSON>, who said he served with the <ORGANIZATION> Marines </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. `` I got it worse in the <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corps </ORGANIZATION> anyway. We'll just sit and wait.'' Some <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> students on spring break had a party at the Holiday Isle hotel. `` I had 10 rooms and I rented them all in about 10 minutes,'' said <PERSON> Alfrieda </PERSON> <PERSON> Bressler </PERSON>, night manager at the <LOCATION> Chesapeake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Motel </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Islamorada </LOCATION>. `` It's not unusual for the bridge to get stuck, but it's usually only for an hour or two. This is the worst I've ever seen it.'' In <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> set up a roadblock to turn back southbound drivers. The <LOCATION> Snake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Creek </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bridge </LOCATION> is expected to remain closed to boat traffic for two to three weeks, restricting boat traffic to those small enough to move under the span, <PERSON> Pinder </PERSON> said.
