<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 233,594 cars and trucks this week, up from last week's 230,813, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday. Automakers produced 241,104 cars and trucks during the same week a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 147,063 cars this week, compared with 147,039 a week ago and 164,212 in the same week in 1987. Truck production for the week was scheduled at 86,531, compared with last week's 83,774 and last year's 76,892. Canadian automakers were to build 26,445 cars this week, compared with 18,884 last week and 17,709 in the same week last year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 19,864, compared with 20,262 last week and 18,734 in the same week last year.
