<HEAD>Dollar Continues Slide; Gold Mixed</HEAD>
<HEAD>Precedes BC-LONDON</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar continued to slide Thursday, reaching levels against the Japanese yen and West German mark not seen for two months as a bearish sentiment pervaded currency markets. Gold prices firmed. <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> quoted a bid price for gold of $ 453.15 a troy ounce as of 4 p.m. EST, up from Wednesday's late bid of $ 451.15 an ounce. Traders said the dollar continued to suffer from comments made Wednesday by <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Feldstein </PERSON>, former chief economic advisor to the president, who said the currency should fall to 120 yen in the near term. In an address at <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Feldstein </PERSON> also predicted the dollar would decline against other currencies over the next several years. `` Those comments are not new, but they triggered losses'' in the dollar, said <PERSON> Earl </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>, a vice president at <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trust </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co </ORGANIZATION>. The dollar, which closed at 125.575 yen in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, last traded at that level in mid-January. Traders said the yen continues to strengthen ahead of the close of the Japanese fiscal year on March 31 and on the expectation that the Japanese economy will forge ahead. The dollar also weakened somewhat on government reports that personal income grew 0.9 percent in February and that personal consumption expenditures grew 0.7 percent during the month. The figures indicated that consumer spending is picking up again, which likely will result in wider trade deficits, said <PERSON> Nigel </PERSON> <PERSON> Green </PERSON>, a trader at <ORGANIZATION> EBC-Amr